assistant: Here’s a very concise summary:

The universe began with the Big Bang about 13.8 billion years ago, expanding and cooling to form atoms. Gravity built stars, where fusion created heavier elements; when stars exploded, those elements seeded new stars and planets. Our solar system formed around 4.6 billion years ago, Earth developed life, and humans emerged to wonder about origins. Today the cosmos keeps expanding, dominated by dark matter and dark energy across billions of galaxies, with Earth as a tiny blue dot.
